main event: Turbulence and mist-like phenomenon observed in front of a cargo ship in Seattle, Washington from December 24-26, 1965.
interesting points: The turbulence/mist extended from the surface to a height of approximately 30-40 feet and had a diameter of around 50 feet.
The turbulence/mist was observed for approximately 10 minutes before slowly dissipating.
No magnetic disturbances, infrared effects, or radio reception effects were noted during the sighting.
The sighting was reported to the Air Force Systems Command (AFSC) and entered into Project Blue Book on January 6, 1966.
The report includes two photographs of the cargo ship docked in the harbor.
sighted object: water turbulence/mist extending from the surface to 30-40 feet in height
